==Player-owned farm==
To efficiently do [[player-owned farm]] on an ironman, you need to purchase a lot of unlocks. This guide will help you do that as fast as possible.

===Before level 64 Farming===
* '''Breeding Pen'''
** Breeding pair of [[Rellekkan cream rabbit]] in the breeding pen (can also use [[Common brown rabbit|normal rabbits]]).
* '''Small Pen'''
** Move rabbits that are bred into small pens.
** Sell all rabbits except the breeding pair (preferably when adolescent).
* '''Medium Pen'''
** 4 [[Sheep (player-owned farm)|sheep]] in each medium pen
** Sell all sheep (preferably when adolescent).
* '''Large Pen'''
** 3 [[bull]]s in each large pen
** Sell all bulls (preferably when adolescent).
''(You can also grow [[common green frog]]s on [[Anachronia]])''

===After level 64 Farming===
The objective now is to unlock the important POF rewards, in the following order:

{| class="wikitable lighttable align-center-1"
!Order
!Unlocks
|-
| 1
| [[Adam Antite]]
|-
| 2
| Medium Pen Breeding
|-
| 3
| Small Pen Breeding
|-
| 4
| Large Pen Breeding
|-
| 5
| [[Master farmer outfit blueprint]]
|-
| 6
| [[Master farmer fragment pack]]
|}
''Make sure that you send off [[Adam Antite]] until you have a breeding pair of [[Carnivorous chinchompa (player-owned farm)|red chinchompas]], [[Yak (player-owned farm)|yaks]], and [[Dragon (player-owned farm)|dragons]]''.

Pens should be setup as follows:
* '''Breeding Pen'''
** Obtain a breeding pair of [[Spider (player-owned farm)|spiders]] by killing spiders within the [[Lumbridge Catacombs]]. '''Do this immediately at 64 Farming as this will be your main source of beans.'''
** Place these spiders in the breeding pen.
** If you have breeding yaks or dragons, replace your spiders with those.
* '''Small Pen'''
** [[Chinchompa (player-owned farm)|Chinchompas]] (preferably [[Carnivorous chinchompa (player-owned farm)|red]]) in the small pens
* '''Medium Pen'''
** Move spiders that are bred into medium pens (do not place food in the medium pens until medium pen breeding is unlocked)
** Sell all bred spiders (preferably when adolescent).
** ''(Once medium pen breeding is unlocked, you can swap out 1 of your medium pens for a breeding pair of [[Zygomite (player-owned farm)|zygomites]] (not [[Gloomshroom zygomite|gloomshrooms]]). You do not need to feed them but can if you want)''
* '''Large Pen'''
** [[Yak (player-owned farm)|Yaks]] > [[Dragon (player-owned farm)|dragons]] in large pens
''Once you have obtained all of the listed shop unlocks, you should stop selling animals as adolescent, and instead let them grow to elders (to maximise XP).''

'''Note:''' If you get a [[Strawberry cow|strawberry]]/[[Vanilla cow|vanilla]]/[[chocolate cow]] from Adam Antite, bank them. You will need them for the [[Contract Claws]] mystery.

==Mining and Smithing training==
This miniguide will explain the quickest way to train your Smithing to 80.

''If you are planning to train smithing past 80, you should do a mixture of Banite smithing and corrupted ores.''

'''Note:''' All Smithing training should be done at the [[Artisans' workshop]], preferably on world 70.

===Collecting the ores & smithing bars===
Collect and smith the following items:

* '''Levels 40-50'''
** Mine 248 [[Adamantite ore]] and 248 [[Luminite]]
** Smith 5 [[Adamant burial set]]
** Smith 1 adamant full helm +2
* '''Levels 50-70'''
** Mine 1750 [[Runite ore]] and 1750 [[Luminite]]
** Smith 18 [[Runite burial set]]
* '''Levels 70-80'''
** Mine 1536 [[Necronium ore]] and 1536 [[Phasmatite]]
** Smith 8 [[Necronium burial set]]
** ''Note: You may need a 9th set if you forget to purchase XP-boosting rewards.''

===Reward upgrades===
Rewards from the [[Artisans' Workshop Reward Shop]] should be purchased in the following order:

